message.content: cs.DM, cs.THEORY, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.SY - The paper presents a mathematical framework to address self-similarity and recursion within the active tile assembly model, which suggests that it belongs to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Theoretical Computer Science (cs.THEORY) sub-categories. The model is also applied to show a recursive assembly of an archetypal self-similar aperiodic tiling, which indicates that it could be relevant to Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
